data.content:
Created both files. Here's a summary:

**`SortableList.razor`** — Renders a `<ul>` with each item showing the `ItemTemplate` content plus Move Up/Move Down buttons. Buttons are disabled at list boundaries.

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — Code-behind with:
- **`@typeparam TItem`** — works with any type
- **Internal copy** — `_items` is cloned from `Items` in `SetParametersAsync`, so the parent's list is never mutated
- **`OnOrderChanged`** — fires after each swap with a read-only snapshot of the reordered list

**Usage** matches your example exactly:
```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { /* ... */ };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
